title: Hit highlighting: SWIRL adds a space before matching terms next to a comma
body:
This behavior is most commonly seen in the Body field (see the example below), but I no reason it couldn't exist also in Title.  The gist is that when we highlight a matching terms that is next to a comma, we insert an extra space before the comma.  We have already completed the query and ranked the results, so the core function of the product is not an issue.  However, our hit highlighting code might need some tightening up soon.  See also Issue #77 

Running this query with the 3 default Google PSE SearchProviders active:  `q=strategic technology consulting`

On the 2nd page of results, there are few examples of this issue, see below.  I have checked some of the original pages, and there is no space before the comma in each case.

Example, result 16:
![Issue 119 - result 16 body](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/98238295/220658992-4001e83c-f06e-487b-b713-04b62bfc0804.png)

Example, result 18:
![Issue 119 - result 18 body](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/98238295/220659058-a3d0bf3e-c504-487f-8b7b-ee7fa17b1336.png)

Example, result 20:
![Issue 119 - result 20 body](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/98238295/220659146-a7c5c259-8b33-4a5b-b4ba-95a97e33bb56.png)

title: Docker searches on MacOS taking ~2 minutes to complete (Swirl 1.8)
body:
In doing some basic testing of Swirl 1.8, it's clear the Docker-ized version is taking longer to return results than before.  Running on a MacBook Pro with an M1 chip, fwiw.

With only the 3 basic PSE SearchProviders plus newsdata.io, here are some search times from 1.8 running in Docker:
```
        "date_created": "2023-01-15T14:33:58.591587-05:00",
        "date_updated": "2023-01-15T14:35:49.267929-05:00",
```

```
        "date_created": "2023-01-15T14:00:27.947574-05:00",
        "date_updated": "2023-01-15T14:02:14.049838-05:00",
```

```
        "date_created": "2023-01-15T13:43:42.819850-05:00",
        "date_updated": "2023-01-15T13:45:19.962150-05:00",
```

These are taken directly from the Search List page in v. 1.8 (http://localhost:8000/swirl/search/)

Not sure what can be done, but if searches take much longer, using Docker on this hardware becomes less and less tenable.  Tagging it as a question for now.  Might also be fodder for a Discussion?

title: Docker shutdown / restart issue with v. 1.8 Swirl?
body:
It appears that doing a ctrl-c to gracefully stop Docker (MacOS, Terminal) doesn't result in rabbitmq being properly terminated ... or, in the shutdown process not fully clearing or deleting the `.swirl` file.

To see this in action:
- Get the Docker version of Swirl 1.8 up and running (do a search to make sure, etc.)
- Issue `CTRL-C` in the Terminal window where you ran `docker compose up`
- Give it a moment or few to finish shutdown, then issue a fresh `docker compose up`
- You'll see this warning about rabbitmq running already:
```
swirl1-8rc-app-1  | Error: rabbitmq appears to be running, please check .swirl or remove it; exiting...
swirl1-8rc-app-1  | Command start reported an error
```

- Docker will continue to bring up Swirl
- Once it's up, do a search (e.g. `?q=tesla`)
- You will get this rather gnarly error in the results window along with a mighty stacktrace:
```
OperationalError at /swirl/search/
[Errno 111] Connection refused
```

To remediate this issue:

- While Docker is still running
- Go the the Docker GUI, Containers > open the container in question > three-dot menu > Open in Terminal
- Remove the `.swirl` file
- Stop Docker
- Restart Docker

Screen grab of the rabbitmq error when starting Docker:
![Docker - 1 8 shut down](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/98238295/212562408-af3b0ccc-f2d8-4ea8-908c-d0ab04b834e0.png)

Screen grab of Operational Error in the UI:
![Docker - 1 8 restart error](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/98238295/212562423-050fa78e-374e-4dfe-9a13-3187ddb786d5.png)

title: PostgreSQL driver Psycopg2 issues
body:
The psycopg2 driver for PostgreSQL has been removed from requirements.txt. This is because PostgreSQL must be installed, and the pg_config executable must be in the path.

If that is the case, simply do:

```
pip install psycopg2
python swirl.py restart core
```

Note that there is error handling to take care of the case where the PostgreSQL connector is requested, but the package is not installed. An error will appear in the message section of the search object.

Three of these explanations indicate that the question mark (?) is required before adding the additional parameter:

The code responsible for generating the text at the top of the Result List page should be update such that the ampersand is presented to users for these 3 options.

title: Can't save date_mixer in a search object due to model validation (MINOR)
body:
# Description

Using SWIRL Search 1.1, if you try to create a search object with "result_mixer": "date mixer", it will fail due to this option not being in the models.py choice list.

# Workaround

Specify the default when creating the search object, then change the mixer when viewing results. For example, if the default URL is:

http://localhost:8000/swirl/results/?search_id=2

And this is not date mixed, manually add the following to the URL:

http://localhost:8000/swirl/results/?search_id=2&result_mixer=date_mixer

# Notes

The result_mixer stored in the search_object is just the default, but it doesn't impact the way data is stored, and isn't validated once results are available.

This will be fixed in 1.1.1.
